OL,6,FFellow party guest Tiffany Ferriday
OL,7,Ftold the court she and Mr Watson had
OL,8,F"clicked" and Wood was "pretty much
OL,9,Fleft out" of conversation.
OL,11,FBut Wood told the court that when she
OL,12,Fdrove Mr Watson home from the party in
OL,13,Fhis car, despite knowing she was over
OL,14,Fthe drink-drive limit, he "flipped"
OL,15,Fand accused her of flirting with other
OL,16,Fmen.
OL,18,FThe student described an argument
OL,19,Fwhich continued when they returned to
OL,20,Fthe house they owned in Oak Street.
